org.xflatdb.xflat

Interface KeyValueTable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConvertingKeyValueTable

    public interface KeyValueTable
    This interface represents a "KeyValue" view to an XFlat table. The KeyValue view allows storing arbitrary convertible objects by key in the database.
    Author:
    Gordon

      • put

        <T> T put(String key,
        T row)
        Puts a value with the given key in the database. If the value already exists, it is overwritten and the old value is returned.
        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        key - The key to which the value is associated.
        row - The new value for the row. Cannot be null.
        Returns:
        The old value for the row, or null if it did not previously exist.

      • findAll

        <T> List<T> findAll(XPathQuery query,
                  Class<T> clazz)
        Gets a list of all the values matching the Xpath query. This is the same as #find(org.xflatdb.xflat.query.XPathQuery) but without the hassle of a cursor.
        Parameters:
        query - The query to match.
        clazz - The type as which the value should be deserialized.
        Returns:
        A list of all the matching values.

      • update
